def priority(current_city: int, distances: np.ndarray, unvisited: set[int]) -> np.ndarray:
    num_cities = unvisited.shape[0]
    priorities = np.zeros(num_cities)
    
    for i in range(num_cities):
        dist = distances[current_city, unvisited[i]]
        priorities[i] = 1.0 / (dist + 1e-5)
    
    return priorities
